cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CE, cs.CR 

This paper is about improving the search quality of an E-Commerce platform using learning to rank algorithms. It focuses on using counterfactual risk minimization (CRM) approach to learn from logged contextual-bandit feedback. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as deep neural network models, which suggests it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, it involves natural language processing techniques to process user queries, which could place it in cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the dataset used, which could place it in cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
